<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 24 at 3:26AM EST  by NWS New York City - Upton</headline>
<description>Light snow is beginning to fall across the region and should
continue through day break. A light coating of accumulation is
expected on area roadways, especially secondaries and untreated
roads. Temperatures are also below freezing which could create
slick spots where snow may have initially melted. Use extra
caution if traveling early this morning as slippery conditions
are expected.</description>
